@startuml
' Epic E6 — Issue and Settle Security
' Context / actor-data-flow view

title E6 — Core Users, Systems, and Data Exchange
left to right direction
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam actorStyle awesome

actor "Issuance Officer" as IO
actor "Issuance Approver /\nTreasury Manager" as AP
actor "Settlement Operations\nAnalyst" as SO
actor "Finance / Accounting\nAnalyst" as FA
actor "Dealer / Investor-side\nSettlement Participant" as DP
actor "Operations Support" as OS

rectangle "Modern Debt Platform" as MDP {
  component "Transaction &\nSecurity Terms" as TERMS
  component "Approval Workflow" as APPROVAL
  component "Issuance Instruction\nService" as IIS
  component "Settlement Status &\nException Management" as SEM
  component "Reconciliation &\nReporting" as REC
  database "Debt Transaction &\nAudit Store" as DB
}

cloud "Security Identifier /\nCUSIP Service" as CUSIP
cloud "Federal Reserve Book-Entry /\nFedwire Securities Interface" as FED
cloud "Cash / General Ledger\nSystems" as GL

IO --> TERMS : Draft transaction terms\nprincipal, dates, product, rate
TERMS --> IO : Validation results\ntransaction ID, status

AP --> APPROVAL : Approval / rejection\ncomments, limits, exceptions
APPROVAL --> AP : Review package\nterms, controls, audit history

SO --> IIS : Generate / submit\nissuance instruction
IIS --> SO : Pre-transmission validation\nand submission status

SO --> SEM : Review settlement status\nresolve exceptions
SEM --> SO : Accepted / pending / rejected\nreason and corrective action

FA --> REC : Run reconciliation\nreview cash and positions
REC --> FA : Proceeds, security quantity,\nbreaks, ledger status

OS --> SEM : Investigate technical or\noperational failure
SEM --> OS : Error context, timestamps,\nmessage IDs, retry status

TERMS --> CUSIP : Security terms request
CUSIP --> TERMS : Security identifier / CUSIP

IIS --> FED : Issuance / settlement instruction\nCUSIP, principal, settlement date, terms
FED --> SEM : Acknowledgment and lifecycle status\naccepted, pending, rejected, settled

DP --> FED : Settlement-side cash /\nsecurities participation
FED --> DP : Book-entry security /\nsettlement confirmation

FED --> GL : Cash settlement entries / status
GL --> REC : Cash and ledger postings
FED --> REC : Final security movement / status

TERMS --> DB : Transaction and security terms
APPROVAL --> DB : Decisions and approvals
IIS --> DB : Instruction payload and version
SEM --> DB : Responses, exceptions, retries
REC --> DB : Reconciliation results

note bottom of FED
Conceptual external infrastructure actor.
Exact interfaces and message formats
must be confirmed during discovery.
end note

legend right
|= Direction |= Typical information |
| User -> Platform | commands, approvals, corrections |
| Platform -> User | statuses, validation, exceptions |
| Platform <-> External | identifiers, instructions, settlement responses |
endlegend
@enduml
